TEXT(EV3(<<'EOT'));
Given \[
f(x) = \frac{ x }{x +   \frac{ $c}{x} }
\]
The derivative function is given by $PAR
\[
f'(x) = \frac{ A x^2 + Bx + C }{ (x^2 +  D  )^2   }
\]
where
$PAR
\(A\) = \{ ans_rule(4)\}
$PAR
\(B\) = \{ ans_rule(4)\}
$PAR
\(C\) = \{ ans_rule(4)\}
$PAR
\(D\) = \{ ans_rule(4)\}

EOT

ANS(num_cmp([0,2*$c,0,$c], relTol=>.1));

